<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/572063-hey-everyone-i-heard-great-things-about">Hey everyone. I heard great things about Yukio Mishima and was wondering if someone could let me know which one of his books would be the best to start with. Would it be this? &#39;Spring Snow&#39;? Also, I am a huge Murakami...are there any similarities?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_572063'><a id="like_count_community_question_572063" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/572063?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F62793.Spring_Snow">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/572063-hey-everyone-i-heard-great-things-about">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/572063-hey-everyone-i-heard-great-things-about">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7366675-morgan"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1590151183i/7366675._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7366675-morgan">Morgan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;m currently reading this book and I would say read his short stories first. Maybe try to find &quot;Patriotism&quot; since that&apos;s the first one I started. He&apos;<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'm currently reading this book and I would say read his short stories first. Maybe try to find "Patriotism" since that's the first one I started. He's an amazing writer, but heavy. I haven't read Murakami yet, so I can't tell you about that. The author I'd compare Mishima the most with in an odd way is an extreme male version of Virginia Woolf. Two writers who couldn't seem fit in and decided to take there own life. However, Mishima is more violent, but in a beautiful poetic kind of way.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

