<div id="review_95504275" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/95504275" />
    <a title="K.D. Absolutely" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2156200-k-d-absolutely"><img alt="K.D. Absolutely" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1471967140p2/2156200.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/95504275?book_show_action=true">Mar 24, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="K.D. Absolutely" class="user" itemprop="url" name="K.D. Absolutely" href="/user/show/2156200-k-d-absolutely">K.D. Absolutely</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to K.D. by: </span>
      501 Must Read Books; 1001 Books You Must Read Before You Die (20
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2156200-k-d-absolutely?shelf=501">501</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer95504275" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12315262229065676465">A story of young tragic love. If you strip the plot to its barest, two young children grew up together. The girl was 2 years older. At 21, she showed affection to the boy but the boy was immature enough to brush it off. At that age and time in Japan, 21 was already old so her parents arranged her to be married to an Imperial prince. After she was betrothed, the boy changed his mind, chased the girl, got her pregnant. Again, during that time in Japan, it was a mortal sin to commit such act to the</span>
  <span id="freeText12315262229065676465" style="display:none">A story of young tragic love. If you strip the plot to its barest, two young children grew up together. The girl was 2 years older. At 21, she showed affection to the boy but the boy was immature enough to brush it off. At that age and time in Japan, 21 was already old so her parents arranged her to be married to an Imperial prince. After she was betrothed, the boy changed his mind, chased the girl, got her pregnant. Again, during that time in Japan, it was a mortal sin to commit such act to the Imperial family. A sin that is punishable by death or seppuku (ritual disembowelment).<br /><br />A story of friendship. The boy, the only son of a rising <i>nouveau-riche</i> family was pretty and did not meet the expectation of his father in terms of being snappy, manly and interested in art of Japanese war and culture. In school, he had only one friend, another aloof boy who was interested in studying law. Their story of friendship was almost lopsided: with the pretty boy almost getting the better side of the bargain. However, the future lawyer stood by his side especially during the love's tragic end. Their story could put you to tears.<br /><br />A story of Japan during the early years (1912 to 1914)of Taishō period (the period of Great Enlightenment). The novel's themes centre on the conflicts in Japanese society caused by westernization in the early 20th century. It was a treat to read how the royal people in Japan lived their lives - their big, their palatial house (the boy residing in a house overlooking a big lake and an island in the middle), their many housemaids, the different annual celebrations (the autumn festivities for example should have been a visual feast as described in the book), etc.<br /><br />This novel, published in 1966, is the first in Yukio Mishima's <b>Sea of Fertility</b> tetralogy. In 1970, after finishing the fourth and final book, he killed himself by doing a <b>seppuku</b> (ritual disembowlment). He was only <b>45</b> years old.<br /><br />As old as I am now.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="12315262229065676465" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

