    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_832092989" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/832092989" />
    <a title="Steven" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4452312-steven"><img alt="Steven" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1449093910p2/4452312.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/832092989?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Steven" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Steven" href="/user/show/4452312-steven">Steven</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4452312-steven?shelf=literature">literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4452312-steven?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4452312-steven?shelf=japanese">japanese</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4452312-steven?shelf=mishima">mishima</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer832092989" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3477533966567621271"><blockquote><i>&quot;The only thing that seemed valid to him was to live for the emotions - gratuitous and unstable, dying only to quicken again, dwindling and flaring without direction or purpose.&quot;</i> (15)</blockquote>I approached Mishima at perhaps an unusual angle, reading first his novel <i>Confessions of a Mask</i>, followed by a collection of his Nō Plays and then his stories. I now thought it was time to read <i>Spring Snow</i>, the first book in his <i>The Sea of Fertility</i> tetralogy (upon completion of which, on 25 November, 1970, Mishima </span>
  <span id="freeText3477533966567621271" style="display:none"><blockquote><i>"The only thing that seemed valid to him was to live for the emotions - gratuitous and unstable, dying only to quicken again, dwindling and flaring without direction or purpose."</i> (15)</blockquote>I approached Mishima at perhaps an unusual angle, reading first his novel <i>Confessions of a Mask</i>, followed by a collection of his Nō Plays and then his stories. I now thought it was time to read <i>Spring Snow</i>, the first book in his <i>The Sea of Fertility</i> tetralogy (upon completion of which, on 25 November, 1970, Mishima committed seppuku [ritualistic suicide] – a harrowing image of which he painted some years before in his visceral short story <i>Patriotism</i>). <br /><br />I was expecting the kind of intensity found in the works by Mishima that I had previously read. In this sense, I was disappointed. <i>Spring Snow</i> is slow-going and carefully drawn-out. It includes a few too many clichés for my liking – you know, the eyes-like-pearls, mouth-like-a-rose-petal, and things-being-fathomless-like-the-sea similes and metaphors. It was definitely worth reading, however; patience in some places is rewarded with lovely passages here and there, and the pace quickens considerably towards the end. I look forward to continuing the Sea of Fertility tetralogy; I already bought the pretty Vintage editions of the next three books, <i>Runaway Horses</i>, <i>The Temple of Dawn</i>, and <i>The Decay of the Angel</i>, to complete the set.<blockquote><i>"If a candle has burned brilliantly but now stands alone in the dark with its flame extinguished, it need no longer fear that its substance will dissolve into hot wax."</i> (166)</blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="3477533966567621271" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


